flowRoot.flowPara: Idea: save images as executables in a portable bytecode.
When compiled and run they could produce an image.
Animation - executable could be run with a time as an input to produce consecutive frames of an animation.
Scalability - using bitmap size as another input would make the image natively scalable.
Near-optimal compression - approaching Kolmogorov complexity of encoded image in the given bytecode.

Performance - image executable could use a set of natively optimized libraries available during runtime (fft, H.264, svg primitives, OpenGL, etc.). When used to draw animation, executable could retain its state to allow inter-frame compression.
Safety - complex image decoding is done in sandbox. Image executable could run in a separate process.
Free-market of encoders - differences between encoding techniquest would promote competition and innovation. Any forseeable encoder could save its output as an image executable.
